W^\prime = \{ g: [-1,1] \rightarrow R | \int_0^1 g(x) d \mu = \frac{1}{2},  \int_{-1}^0 g(x) d \mu = - \frac{1}{2}\}
 \implies || f||_{C/W} = \inf_{g \in W^\prime} \sup_{x \in [-1,1]} |g(x)| = \inf_{g \in W^\prime} ||g ||_\infty
 || g||_\infty = || g||_\infty \mu([0,1]) \geq \int_0^1 g d \mu = \frac{1}{2}
 \implies ||f||_{C/W} \geq \frac{1}{2}
